# Cline Rules - Quick Reference

# Full docs: CLINERULES.md, AGENTS.md

## Project
Jekyll portfolio site - DynamicCareerCanvas

## Stack
Jekyll, YAML data, SCSS, Vanilla JS, GitHub Pages

## Core Rules

### Must Follow
- Read .ai/CONTEXT.md before starting
- NO frameworks (React, Vue, jQuery, etc.)
- Content in YAML files (_data/)
- Use CSS variables
- Mobile-first responsive
- Support light/dark mode
- Test builds: bundle exec jekyll build
- Include AI attribution in commits

### File Structure
_data/ - YAML content
_includes/components/ - UI components
_layouts/ - Page templates
_sass/ - Styles
assets/ - Static files

### Code Style

YAML:
company: "Name"
date: "YYYY-MM"

HTML/Liquid:
<div class="component-name">
  {{ data.field }}
</div>

SCSS:
.component {
  property: var(--variable);

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    // mobile
  }
}

JavaScript:
// ES6+, no frameworks
const fn = () => {};

### Workflow
1. Plan approach
2. Read context files
3. Make changes
4. Test build
5. Verify in browser
6. Commit with attribution

### Testing
